posts.post_title: Lower end T206 LOTS, HOFers, commons w/ markings, and others
posts.post_content:
Hello all,
I am putting together some stuff to sell this weekend as I have upgraded a few spots in my stack and need to put together a little money for Vegas.

T206 10 card lot.  See scans.  MOVED TO EBAY

Wilson: Old Mill writting on back, very light crease bottom left
Bates: Sovereign 150: W. Doyle written on back, clean card
Tenney: SC 150, 25, vertical crease, Mr. Roteman stamp on back, soiled
Puttman Louisville: P350, very light pencil mark on back, couple very short light creases on front
MOVED TO EBAY



T206 Tinker (bat on) and Evers (CHI): MOVED TO EBAY
These feel a little short so I am going to sell them as trims.  Evers has something on the front (old glue?).  Both have wear, Tinker has a creses.  Both are P350-460.

Thanks,
Bob
